3.3. Greenhouse Gas Data
We assessed the reconstructed hyperspectral data’s utility
for predicting concentrations of NO2, CH4, and CO2.
These GHG products were spatiotemporally mapped to the
HySpecNet-11k dataset based on the spatial footprint of En-
MAP patches under application-specific time windows:
• Sentinel-5P [11]:
– NO2 retrievals (molm−2) were matched within ±1
day, reflecting its shorter atmospheric lifetime [17].
This yielded data for about 88% of the EnMAP
patches.
– CH4 measurements (ppb) were matched within ±7
